# Java Docker Containers

## Base Images
- Build stage: `eclipse-temurin:21-jdk-alpine`
- Runtime stage: `eclipse-temurin:21-jre-alpine`
- Minimal: `gcr.io/distroless/java21-debian12` for production
- Pin image digests for reproducibility in production

## Multi-Stage Builds
```dockerfile
FROM eclipse-temurin:21-jdk-alpine AS build
WORKDIR /app
COPY . .
RUN ./mvnw -DskipTests package

FROM eclipse-temurin:21-jre-alpine
WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=build /app/target/*.jar app.jar
ENTRYPOINT ["java", "-jar", "app.jar"]
```

## JVM Memory
- Use container-aware JVM flags (default since Java 10)
- `-XX:MaxRAMPercentage=75.0` instead of fixed `-Xmx`
- `-XX:+UseContainerSupport` (enabled by default)

## Alternatives to Dockerfile
- Jib: `jib-maven-plugin` or `jib-gradle-plugin` -- builds OCI images without Docker daemon
- Spring Boot Buildpacks: `./mvnw spring-boot:build-image`
- Both produce layered, reproducible images

## Security
- Run as non-root user: `USER 1001`
- No secrets in image layers or build args
- Scan images with Trivy or Snyk
- Minimal base images: remove shells and package managers where possible

## Layers
- Spring Boot layered JARs for efficient Docker caching
- Separate dependency layers from application code
- `COPY --from=build /app/target/extracted/dependencies/ ./`

## Health Checks
```dockerfile
HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=3s \
  CMD wget --spider -q http://localhost:8080/actuator/health || exit 1
```
